<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Lemna</i> spp., <i>Spirodela</i> spp., <i>Wolffia</i> spp. or <i>Wolffiella</i> spp. are dominant herbs on the water surface or characteristically present in the herbaceous layer with <i>Azolla</i> <i>filiculoides</i>, <i>Azolla</i> <i>mexicana</i> and <i>Egeria</i> <i>densa</i>. Emergent plants may be present at low cover, including <i>Myriophyllum</i> <i>aquaticum</i> or <i>Scirpus</i> spp. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs 0.3-8mm in size; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Seasonal and perennial freshwater habitats with still water or on ground surfaces after water levels have dropped. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Lemna aequinoctialis, L. minor, L. trisulca, Spirodela polyrrhiza, S. punctata, Wolffia globosa, Wolffiella lingulata,</i> and <i>W. oblonga</i> as OBL plants. </div>
</div>

		
